# Tailwind CSS 4 Standards & Conventions

Styling in `frontend/` is utility-first Tailwind CSS 4.

## Allowed CSS Entry (exception)

**Exactly one** CSS entry file is required and allowed, e.g. `frontend/src/index.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

/* Optional design tokens */
@theme {
  /* only if needed — prefer default Tailwind scale */
}
```

Import that file once from the app entry (`main.tsx`). No other custom CSS files. No `style={{}}` in components. No `@apply` for component classes — extract React components instead.

Do not require a legacy `tailwind.config.js` for Core. If a config file exists, keep it minimal; prefer `@import "tailwindcss"` + `@theme` for v4.

## Utilities Only in Components

```tsx
// ✅
<button className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:outline-none transition-colors">
  Create Ticket
</button>

// ❌
<button style={{ backgroundColor: 'blue' }}>Create Ticket</button>
<button className="btn-primary">Create Ticket</button>
```

## Layout

Mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`). `flex` for 1D, `grid` for 2D; prefer `gap-*` over sibling margins. Page shell: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`; root `min-h-screen`.

## Status & Priority Colors

Use these exact mappings everywhere status/priority appears:

| Status | Classes |
|---|---|
| Open | `bg-gray-100 text-gray-800` |
| In Progress | `bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800` |
| Resolved | `bg-green-100 text-green-800` |
| Closed | `bg-purple-100 text-purple-800` |
| Cancelled | `bg-red-100 text-red-800` |

| Priority | Classes |
|---|---|
| low | `bg-blue-100 text-blue-800` |
| medium | `bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800` |
| high | `bg-red-100 text-red-800` |

Primary actions: `bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white`.

Centralize in a const map (e.g. `STATUS_STYLES`) — do not invent alternate palette classes per screen.

**Transition buttons:** only for reachable next statuses; `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed` while pending; terminal `Closed`/`Cancelled` → badge only, no buttons.

## Typography & Spacing

- Titles: `text-2xl font-bold` / sections `text-xl font-semibold` / cards `text-lg font-medium`
- Meta: `text-sm text-gray-500`; body `text-base` / `text-gray-700`
- Truncate titles with `truncate`; descriptions `line-clamp-2` / `line-clamp-3`
- Spacing: `p-4`/`p-6`, `space-y-4` in forms, `gap-6` between sections, page `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-6`
- Cards: `rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm`
- Avoid arbitrary values (`w-[137px]`) unless no scale token fits

## Forms & Focus

Labeled inputs; error → red border/ring + `role="alert"` message. Every control needs hover/focus/disabled. Never use `outline-none` without `focus:ring-*`.

```tsx
className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium
  hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:outline-none
  disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors"
```

Icon-only buttons: `<span className="sr-only">…</span>`. Body text on white no lighter than `text-gray-600`. Skeletons `animate-pulse`; spinners `animate-spin`.

## Dark Mode

**Out of scope for Core.** Do not add `dark:` variants unless a Stretch task explicitly asks. If added later, use a class-based variant consistently and pair every light utility with a `dark:` counterpart.

## Validation Checklist

1. ✅ Single Tailwind v4 CSS entry with `@import "tailwindcss"` — no other custom CSS
2. ✅ No `@apply`, no inline styles
3. ✅ Mobile-first responsive prefixes
4. ✅ Hover/focus/disabled on interactive elements; focus ring always present
5. ✅ Exact status/priority color maps
6. ✅ Terminal statuses render no transition buttons
7. ✅ No dark mode unless explicitly requested
8. ✅ WCAG AA: no informational text lighter than `gray-600` on white
